prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF NASA IS SOLICITING PROPOSALS FOR SCIENTIFIC INSTRUMENTS THAT MIGHT REVEAL ANSWERS ABOUT LUNAR RESOURCES THAT COULD SUPPORT THE AGENCY'S JOURNEY TO MARS. NASA WOULD SPONSOR THE INSTRUMENTS TO FLY ON A LUNAR ORBITER DESIGNED BY THE KOREA AEROSPACE RESEARCH INSTITUTE (KARI). THE SPACECRAFT, THE KOREA PATHFINDER LUNAR ORBITER (KPLO), IS SCHEDULED TO LAUNCH IN DECEMBER 2018, AND IS PART OF KARI'S KOREA LUNAR EXPLORATION PROGRAM, WHICH AIMS TO ROBOTICALLY EXPLORE THE MOON THROUGH A SERIES OF ORBITER AND LANDER MISSIONS, STARTING WITH THE KPLO. KARI, HEADQUARTERED IN DAEJEON, SOUTH KOREA, PROVIDED NASA WITH ABOUT 33 POUNDS (15 KILOGRAMS) OF PAYLOAD MASS ABOARD THE KPLO, WHICH IS SCHEDULED TO LAUNCH INTO LUNAR ORBIT IN DECEMBER 2018. IN SEPTEMBER 2016, NASA ISSUED A SOLICITATION SEEKING SCIENCE INSTRUMENTS THAT COULD INCREASE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF THE DISTRIBUTION OF VOLATILES, SUCH AS WATER, INCLUDING THE MOVEMENT OF SUCH RESOURCES TOWARD PERMANENTLY SHADOWED REGIONS AND HOW THEY BECOME TRAPPED THERE. SHADOWCAM WILL MAP THE REFLECTANCE WITHIN THE PERMANENTLY SHADOWED REGIONS TO SEARCH FOR EVIDENCE OF FROST OR ICE DEPOSITS. THE INSTRUMENT'S OPTICAL CAMERA IS BASED ON THE LUNAR RECONNAISSANCE ORBITER NARROW ANGLE CAMERA, BUT IS 800 TIMES MORE SENSITIVE, ALLOWING IT TO OBTAIN HIGH-RESOLUTION, HIGH SIGNAL-TO-NOISE IMAGING OF THE MOON'S PERMANENTLY SHADOWED REGIONS. SHADOWCAM WILL OBSERVE THE PSRS MONTHLY TO DETECT SEASONAL CHANGES AND MEASURE THE TERRAIN INSIDE THE CRATERS, INCLUDING THE DISTRIBUTION OF BOULDERS. NASA'S ADVANCED EXPLORATION SYSTEMS DIVISION (AES) LED THE PAYLOAD SOLICITATION AND SELECTION FOR THE NASA INSTRUMENT ON KPLO. A DIVISION OF THE HUMAN EXPLORATION AND OPERATIONS MISSION DIRECTORATE, AES USES INNOVATIVE APPROACHES AND PUBLIC-PRIVATE PARTNERSHIPS TO RAPIDLY DEVELOP PROTOTYPE SYSTEMS, ADVANCE KEY CAPABILITIES, AND VALIDATE OPERATIONAL CONCEPTS FOR FUTURE HUMAN MISSIONS BEYOND EARTH ORBIT. THROUGH THIS PARTNERSHIP OPPORTUNITY WITH KARI, AES IS ADDRESSING KEY LUNAR SKGS WHILE COMPLEMENTING KARI'S PRIMARY MISSION OBJECTIVES AND INSTRUMENTS.

prime_awardee_parent_name: THE REGENTS OF THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO
prime_awardee_business_types: U.S. State Government,Educational Institution,State Controlled Institution of Higher Learning
prime_award_base_transaction_description: PRODUCTION OF LARGE POPULATIONS OF HEMATOPOIETIC STEM CELLS (HSCS) IN MICROGRAVITY TO TREAT SERIOUS MEDICAL CONDITIONS INCLUDING BLOOD CANCERS (LEUKEMIAS, LYMPHOMAS, MULTIPLE MYELOMA), FATAL BLOOD DISORDERS, AND SEVERE IMMUNE DISEASES.
prime_award_naics_description: ALL OTHER PROFESSIONAL, SCIENTIFIC, AND TECHNICAL SERVICES
subawardee_name: THE REGENTS OF THE UNIV. OF COLORADO
subawardee_business_types: U.S. STATE GOVERNMENT,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,STATE CONTROLLED INSTITUTION OF HIGHER LEARNING
subaward_description:
STATEMENT OF WORK

INTRODUCTION/BACKGROUND
CLINIMMUNE LABS (DR. FREED, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND CO-PRINCIPAL INVESTIGATOR ON THIS PROPOSAL) IS A 23,000-SF CLINICAL AND RESEARCH LABORATORY THAT INCLUDES THE HISTOCOMPATIBILITY LAB, THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO CORD BLOOD BANK, THE STEM CELL LAB (HEMATOPOIETIC AND MESENCHYMAL STEM CELLS AND CAR T CELLS) AND FLOW CYTOMETRY. THE LAB IS FDA-LICENSED AND ACCREDITED BY ASHI, FACT, AABB, CAP, AND CLIA. CLINIMMUNE HAS A STAFF OF 70 EMPLOYEES SKILLED IN ALL ASPECTS OF HLA TESTING AND STEM CELL TRANSPLANTS AND PERFORMS 20,000 HLA TESTS AND >200 STEM CELL TRANSPLANTS ANNUALLY. SINCE ITS INCEPTION, CLINIMMUNE HAS PERFORMED >2000 STEM CELL TRANSPLANTS IN HUMANS AND WAS ONLY THE SECOND CORD BLOOD BANK TO BE LICENSED BY THE FDA.

IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE AEROSPACE ENGINEERING SCIENCES DIVISION AT CU-BOULDER, WE ARE HYPOTHESIZING THAT GROWING HEMATOPOIETIC STEM CELLS IN MICROGRAVITY MAY ALLOW A MUCH GREATER DEGREE OF EXPANSION TO OCCUR THAN ON EARTH, WHILE RETAINING THE DESIRED CELLULAR POPULATIONS THAT ENABLE SUCCESSFUL TRANSPLANTATION. THE AEROSPACE AND ENGINEERING SCIENCES DIVISION WILL DEVELOP SPECIALIZED BIOREACTOR TECHNOLOGY THAT WILL BE DEPLOYED ON A COMMERCIAL SPACE STATION AND SUPPORT THE EXPANSION OF CORD BLOOD OR MOBILIZED PERIPHERAL BLOOD HSCS COLLECTED ON EARTH, CRYOPRESERVED, AND TRANSPORTED FROZEN TO THE SPACE STATION PLATFORM. THE OVERALL GOAL OF THIS PROJECT IS TO DEPLOY AN ARRAY OF STEM CELL EXPANSION BIOREACTORS ON ONE OR MORE SPACE STATIONS TO PRODUCE LARGE NUMBERS OF STEM CELL TRANSPLANT UNITS THAT CAN BE CRYOPRESERVED, RETURNED TO EARTH, AND USED CLINICALLY TO TREAT AN ASSORTMENT OF MEDICAL CONDITIONS IN PATIENTS WORLDWIDE. IF SUCCESSFUL, THE SAME IN-SPACE STEM CELL PRODUCTION TECHNOLOGY MAY ALSO BE USED FOR FUTURE APPLICATIONS IN BIOREGENERATIVE MEDICINE.

SCOPE OF WORK
AS A PART OF THIS WORK, CLINIMMUNES ROLE IS TO ISOLATE AND PURIFY CLINICAL GRADE CD34+ STEM CELLS FOR THE STUDY ALONG WITH GENE EDITED CELLS FOR THE SECOND FLIGHT STUDY. CLINIMMUNE WILL CHARACTERIZE THE CELLS BEFORE AND AFTER EXPANSION USING SEVERAL IN VITRO AND IN VIVO ASSAYS FOR HSC, INCLUDING THE COLONY FORMING ASSAY TO DETECT MULTIPLE LINEAGES AND A MOUSE ENGRAFTMENT ASSAY. INCLUDED IN THIS WILL BE THE NECESSARY FLOW CYTOMETRIC ASSAYS TO ANALYSE THE HSC BOTH BEFORE AND AFTER EXPANSION IN SPACE AND SUBSEQUENT CRYOPRESERVATION. WE WILL ALSO BE PROVIDING CONSULTATION ADVICE ON THE PROJECT THROUGHOUT ITS DURATION, INCLUDING TECHNICAL AND BUSINESS SUPPORT AS REQUIRED BY NASA REQUIREMENTS.

PERIOD OF PERFORMANCE
THIS WORK WILL OCCUR BETWEEN JUNE 1ST, 2022 AND MAY 31ST, 2025.

PLACE OF PERFORMANCE
WORK WILL BE PERFORMED PRIMARILY AT CLINIMMUNE (BIOSCIENCE II). ALL MOUSE MODEL WORK FOR DETERMINING THE FUNCTIONAL STATUS POST EXPANSION WILL BE PERFORMED WITHIN THE RESEARCH BUILDINGS ON THE ANSCHUTZ CAMPUS AT UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO.

WORK REQUIREMENTS
THE FOLLOWING IS AN ITEMIZED LIST OF WORK REQUIREMENTS.
1. BEFORE THE FIRST FLIGHT EXPERIMENT, PROVISION OF CD34+ ISOLATED CELLS FOR CU-BOULDERS BIOREACTOR TESTING AND OPTIMIZATION.
2. CHARACTERIZATION OF CELL MATURITY AND LINEAGE DIFFERENTIATION BEFORE AND AFTER BIOREACTOR EXPANSION DURING PRE-FLIGHT EXPERIMENTS AND PRE AND POST THE FIRST FLIGHT.
3. FOR THE SECOND FLIGHT, PROVISION OF GENE EDITED CD34+ ISOLATED CELLS FOR EXPANSION ALONG WITH PRE AND POST-FLIGHT QUALITY ASSESSMENT OF CELLS EXPANDED IN SPACE VS THOSE EXPANDED ON THE GROUND.
4. FUNCTIONAL MOUSE ASSAYS TO ASSESS REPOPULATION OF THE HEMATOPOIETIC STEM CELL COMPARTMENTS.

SCHEDULE/MILESTONES/TASKS
CD34+ ISOLATION IS CURRENTLY ONGOING (EXPECTED TO CONTINUE INDEFINITELY). CELLS WILL BE PROVIDED STARTING IN JUNE OF 2022 TO THE AEROSPACE DIVISION TO BEGIN PRE-FLIGHT TRIALS. TESTING WILL OCCUR WHEN NECESSARY BASED ON BIOREACTOR EXPANSION AND SPACE FLIGHT TIMING.

prime_award_program_activities_funding_t: 0001: DEEP SPACE EXPLORATION SYSTEMS (DIRECT);0001: DEEP SPACE EXPLORATION SYSTEMS DIRECT);0001: EXPLORATION (DIRECT)
prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF NEXTSTEP NRA AWARD.  THIS NEXTSTEP CONTRACT BUILDS UPON THE SUCCESS OF COMMERCIAL ORBITAL TRANSPORTATION SERVICES SPACE ACT AGREEMENT DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM AND AN EXISTING INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION (ISS) COMMERCIAL RESUPPLY SERVICES (CRS) CONTRACT. ORBITAL HAS SUCCESSFULLY TRANSITIONED FROM COTS TO THE CRS PROGRAM, FLYING THREE VERY SUCCESSFUL PRESSURIZED CARGO RESUPPLY MISSIONS TO THE ISS, USING THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT. ORBITAL ALSO SUCCESSFULLY DEVELOPED SPACECRAFT FOR SOLAR SYSTEM EXPLORATION TO INCLUDE THE CURRENTLY OPERATIONAL DAWN MISSION. THIS MISSION WAS LAUNCHED IN SEPTEMBER 2007, COMPLETED ITS RENDEZVOUS MISSION AT VESTA IN JULY 2012 AND IS EN ROUTE TO CERES IN EARLY 2015.  WITH SPACE AGENCY BUDGETS CONTINUING TO BE TIGHT, EXPLORATION PLANS NEED TO EMPHASIZE EVOLUTION OF EXISTING SYSTEMS, WHERE COST AND SCHEDULE IS BETTER CONTROLLED, AND DEVELOPMENT RISK REDUCED. SPECIFICALLY, ELEMENTS OF THE CURRENT ISS, INCLUDING CYGNUS, CAN BE EVOLVED TO SUPPORT MORE DISTANT SPACE DESTINATIONS. TO SUPPORT THESE ENDEAVORS, ORBITAL CONTRIBUTES TO THE DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCT IMPROVEMENT OF CYGNUS AND TO NEXTSTEP ACTIVITIES AND HAVE INVESTED IN THE COTS CRS PUBLIC-PRIVATE PARTNERSHIP ENDEAVOR.  ORBITAL'S EXPLORATION AUGMENTATION MODULE (BAM) ARCHITECTURE USES A MODULAR, BUILDING BLOCK APPROACH THAT LEVERAGES THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT TO EXPAND CISLUNAR AND LONG DURATION DEEP SPACE TRANSIT HABITATION CAPABILITIES AND TECHNOLOGIES CRITICAL TO NASAS LONG-TERM EXPLORATION GOALS.  ORBITALS ARCHITECTURE CONCEPT BLENDS IN-PRODUCTION HARDWARE WITH ADAPTATION, EVOLUTION, PLANNING, AND FORWARD THINKING. CYGNUS WILL SERVE AS A MODULAR HABITAT AND TEST PLATFORM FOR QUALIFYING TECHNOLOGIES IN A DISTANT RETROGRADE ORBIT (DRO) OR IN A LOW EARTH ORBIT (LEO), EITHER WHILE ATTACHED TO THE ISS OR AS A FREE-FLYER. USING THE EXISTING, OPERATIONAL CYGNUS TO PERFORM THESE MISSIONS HAS THE ADVANTAGE OF DECREASING OVERALL DEVELOPMENT TIME AND COSTS, AND FREEING UP RESOURCES THAT WOULD BE SPENT ON DEVELOPING A SPACECRAFT TO FOCUS ON CULTIVATING MISSION ENABLING TECHNOLOGIES.  THE GOAL IS TO HAVE A CYGNUS DERIVED EAM DEPLOYED IN CISLUNAR SPACE BEFORE 2020. THIS SPACECRAFT WILL BE THE FIRST BUILDING BLOCK IN SUPPORTING BOTH COMMERCIAL MARKETS AND GOVERNMENT OBJECTIVES. THE PROPOSED EFFORT FOR THIS NEXTSTEP BAA PHASE I, INVOLVES DEFINING AN EAM ARCHITECTURE AND CONCEPT OF OPERATIONS (CONOPS) THAT ADDRESSES COMMERCIAL MARKETS AND NASA EXPLORATION OBJECTIVES, TECHNOLOGY MATURATION PLANNING AND INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT, AND TO IDENTIFY TECHNOLOGIES THAT CAN BE IMPLEMENTED AND DEMONSTRATED IN THE ISSILEO ENVIRONMENT WITHIN THE NEXT THREE YEARS.  TO MATURE HABITATION TECHNOLOGIES, THE CONTRACTOR WILL IDENTIFY STATE OF THE ART (SOA) TECHNOLOGIES ACROSS NASA TECHNOLOGY AREAS (TAS) DEFINED IN THE NASA TECHNOLOGY ROADMAP.  FOCUS WILL BE ON MATURATION OF THE FOLLOWING TECHNOLOGIES    ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL AND LIFE SUPPORT SYSTEMS    ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING    SAFETY AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE AND HABITATION    THERMAL CONTROL SYSTEMS    AUTONOMOUS HABITATION SYSTEMS    NAVIGATION    SYSTEMS MANAGEMENT    DOCKING AND CAPTURE    MECHANISMS AND DEPLOYABLE HABITATION ELEMENTS

prime_award_program_activities_funding_t: 0001: DEEP SPACE EXPLORATION SYSTEMS (DIRECT);0001: DEEP SPACE EXPLORATION SYSTEMS DIRECT);0001: EXPLORATION (DIRECT)
prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF NEXTSTEP NRA AWARD.  THIS NEXTSTEP CONTRACT BUILDS UPON THE SUCCESS OF COMMERCIAL ORBITAL TRANSPORTATION SERVICES SPACE ACT AGREEMENT DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM AND AN EXISTING INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION (ISS) COMMERCIAL RESUPPLY SERVICES (CRS) CONTRACT. ORBITAL HAS SUCCESSFULLY TRANSITIONED FROM COTS TO THE CRS PROGRAM, FLYING THREE VERY SUCCESSFUL PRESSURIZED CARGO RESUPPLY MISSIONS TO THE ISS, USING THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT. ORBITAL ALSO SUCCESSFULLY DEVELOPED SPACECRAFT FOR SOLAR SYSTEM EXPLORATION TO INCLUDE THE CURRENTLY OPERATIONAL DAWN MISSION. THIS MISSION WAS LAUNCHED IN SEPTEMBER 2007, COMPLETED ITS RENDEZVOUS MISSION AT VESTA IN JULY 2012 AND IS EN ROUTE TO CERES IN EARLY 2015.  WITH SPACE AGENCY BUDGETS CONTINUING TO BE TIGHT, EXPLORATION PLANS NEED TO EMPHASIZE EVOLUTION OF EXISTING SYSTEMS, WHERE COST AND SCHEDULE IS BETTER CONTROLLED, AND DEVELOPMENT RISK REDUCED. SPECIFICALLY, ELEMENTS OF THE CURRENT ISS, INCLUDING CYGNUS, CAN BE EVOLVED TO SUPPORT MORE DISTANT SPACE DESTINATIONS. TO SUPPORT THESE ENDEAVORS, ORBITAL CONTRIBUTES TO THE DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCT IMPROVEMENT OF CYGNUS AND TO NEXTSTEP ACTIVITIES AND HAVE INVESTED IN THE COTS CRS PUBLIC-PRIVATE PARTNERSHIP ENDEAVOR.  ORBITAL'S EXPLORATION AUGMENTATION MODULE (BAM) ARCHITECTURE USES A MODULAR, BUILDING BLOCK APPROACH THAT LEVERAGES THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT TO EXPAND CISLUNAR AND LONG DURATION DEEP SPACE TRANSIT HABITATION CAPABILITIES AND TECHNOLOGIES CRITICAL TO NASAS LONG-TERM EXPLORATION GOALS. prime_award_program_activities_funding_t: 0001: DEEP SPACE EXPLORATION SYSTEMS (DIRECT);0001: DEEP SPACE EXPLORATION SYSTEMS DIRECT);0001: EXPLORATION (DIRECT)
prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF NEXTSTEP NRA AWARD.  THIS NEXTSTEP CONTRACT BUILDS UPON THE SUCCESS OF COMMERCIAL ORBITAL TRANSPORTATION SERVICES SPACE ACT AGREEMENT DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM AND AN EXISTING INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION (ISS) COMMERCIAL RESUPPLY SERVICES (CRS) CONTRACT. ORBITAL HAS SUCCESSFULLY TRANSITIONED FROM COTS TO THE CRS PROGRAM, FLYING THREE VERY SUCCESSFUL PRESSURIZED CARGO RESUPPLY MISSIONS TO THE ISS, USING THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT. ORBITAL ALSO SUCCESSFULLY DEVELOPED SPACECRAFT FOR SOLAR SYSTEM EXPLORATION TO INCLUDE THE CURRENTLY OPERATIONAL DAWN MISSION. THIS MISSION WAS LAUNCHED IN SEPTEMBER 2007, COMPLETED ITS RENDEZVOUS MISSION AT VESTA IN JULY 2012 AND IS EN ROUTE TO CERES IN EARLY 2015.  WITH SPACE AGENCY BUDGETS CONTINUING TO BE TIGHT, EXPLORATION PLANS NEED TO EMPHASIZE EVOLUTION OF EXISTING SYSTEMS, WHERE COST AND SCHEDULE IS BETTER CONTROLLED, AND DEVELOPMENT RISK REDUCED. SPECIFICALLY, ELEMENTS OF THE CURRENT ISS, INCLUDING CYGNUS, CAN BE EVOLVED TO SUPPORT MORE DISTANT SPACE DESTINATIONS. TO SUPPORT THESE ENDEAVORS, ORBITAL CONTRIBUTES TO THE DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCT IMPROVEMENT OF CYGNUS AND TO NEXTSTEP ACTIVITIES AND HAVE INVESTED IN THE COTS CRS PUBLIC-PRIVATE PARTNERSHIP ENDEAVOR.  ORBITAL'S EXPLORATION AUGMENTATION MODULE (BAM) ARCHITECTURE USES A MODULAR, BUILDING BLOCK APPROACH THAT LEVERAGES THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT TO EXPAND CISLUNAR AND LONG DURATION DEEP SPACE TRANSIT HABITATION CAPABILITIES AND TECHNOLOGIES CRITICAL TO NASAS LONG-TERM EXPLORATION GOALS.  ORBITALS ARCHITECTURE CONCEPT BLENDS IN-PRODUCTION HARDWARE WITH ADAPTATION, EVOLUTION, PLANNING, AND FORWARD THINKING. CYGNUS WILL SERVE AS A MODULAR HABITAT AND TEST PLATFORM FOR QUALIFYING TECHNOLOGIES IN A DISTANT RETROGRADE ORBIT (DRO) OR IN A LOW EARTH ORBIT (LEO), EITHER WHILE ATTACHED TO THE ISS OR AS A FREE-FLYER. USING THE EXISTING, OPERATIONAL CYGNUS TO PERFORM THESE MISSIONS HAS THE ADVANTAGE OF DECREASING OVERALL DEVELOPMENT TIME AND COSTS, AND FREEING UP RESOURCES THAT WOULD BE SPENT ON DEVELOPING A SPACECRAFT TO FOCUS ON CULTIVATING MISSION ENABLING TECHNOLOGIES.  THE GOAL IS TO HAVE A CYGNUS DERIVED EAM DEPLOYED IN CISLUNAR SPACE BEFORE 2020. THIS SPACECRAFT WILL BE THE FIRST BUILDING BLOCK IN SUPPORTING BOTH COMMERCIAL MARKETS AND GOVERNMENT OBJECTIVES. THE PROPOSED EFFORT FOR THIS NEXTSTEP BAA PHASE I, INVOLVES DEFINING AN EAM ARCHITECTURE AND CONCEPT OF OPERATIONS (CONOPS) THAT ADDRESSES COMMERCIAL MARKETS AND NASA EXPLORATION OBJECTIVES, TECHNOLOGY MATURATION PLANNING AND INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT, AND TO IDENTIFY TECHNOLOGIES THAT CAN BE IMPLEMENTED AND DEMONSTRATED IN THE ISSILEO ENVIRONMENT WITHIN THE NEXT THREE YEARS.  TO MATURE HABITATION TECHNOLOGIES, THE CONTRACTOR WILL IDENTIFY STATE OF THE ART (SOA) TECHNOLOGIES ACROSS NASA TECHNOLOGY AREAS (TAS) DEFINED IN THE NASA TECHNOLOGY ROADMAP.  FOCUS WILL BE ON MATURATION OF THE FOLLOWING TECHNOLOGIES    ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL AND LIFE SUPPORT SYSTEMS    ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING    SAFETY AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE AND HABITATION    THERMAL CONTROL SYSTEMS    AUTONOMOUS HABITATION SYSTEMS    NAVIGATION    SYSTEMS MANAGEMENT    DOCKING AND CAPTURE    MECHANISMS AND DEPLOYABLE HABITATION ELEMENTS

prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF NEXTSTEP NRA AWARD.  THIS NEXTSTEP CONTRACT BUILDS UPON THE SUCCESS OF COMMERCIAL ORBITAL TRANSPORTATION SERVICES SPACE ACT AGREEMENT DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM AND AN EXISTING INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION (ISS) COMMERCIAL RESUPPLY SERVICES (CRS) CONTRACT. ORBITAL HAS SUCCESSFULLY TRANSITIONED FROM COTS TO THE CRS PROGRAM, FLYING THREE VERY SUCCESSFUL PRESSURIZED CARGO RESUPPLY MISSIONS TO THE ISS, USING THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT. ORBITAL ALSO SUCCESSFULLY DEVELOPED SPACECRAFT FOR SOLAR SYSTEM EXPLORATION TO INCLUDE THE CURRENTLY OPERATIONAL DAWN MISSION. THIS MISSION WAS LAUNCHED IN SEPTEMBER 2007, COMPLETED ITS RENDEZVOUS MISSION AT VESTA IN JULY 2012 AND IS EN ROUTE TO CERES IN EARLY 2015.  WITH SPACE AGENCY BUDGETS CONTINUING TO BE TIGHT, EXPLORATION PLANS NEED TO EMPHASIZE EVOLUTION OF EXISTING SYSTEMS, WHERE COST AND SCHEDULE IS BETTER CONTROLLED, AND DEVELOPMENT RISK REDUCED. SPECIFICALLY, ELEMENTS OF THE CURRENT ISS, INCLUDING CYGNUS, CAN BE EVOLVED TO SUPPORT MORE DISTANT SPACE DESTINATIONS. TO SUPPORT THESE ENDEAVORS, ORBITAL CONTRIBUTES TO THE DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCT IMPROVEMENT OF CYGNUS AND TO NEXTSTEP ACTIVITIES AND HAVE INVESTED IN THE COTS CRS PUBLIC-PRIVATE PARTNERSHIP ENDEAVOR.  ORBITAL'S EXPLORATION AUGMENTATION MODULE (BAM) ARCHITECTURE USES A MODULAR, BUILDING BLOCK APPROACH THAT LEVERAGES THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT TO EXPAND CISLUNAR AND LONG DURATION DEEP SPACE TRANSIT HABITATION CAPABILITIES AND TECHNOLOGIES CRITICAL TO NASAS LONG-TERM EXPLORATION GOALS.  ORBITALS ARCHITECTURE CONCEPT BLENDS IN-PRODUCTION HARDWARE WITH ADAPTATION, EVOLUTION, PLANNING, AND FORWARD THINKING. CYGNUS WILL SERVE AS A MODULAR HABITAT AND TEST PLATFORM FOR QUALIFYING TECHNOLOGIES IN A DISTANT RETROGRADE ORBIT (DRO) OR IN A LOW EARTH ORBIT (LEO), EITHER WHILE ATTACHED TO THE ISS OR AS A FREE-FLYER. USING THE EXISTING, OPERATIONAL CYGNUS TO PERFORM THESE MISSIONS HAS THE ADVANTAGE OF DECREASING OVERALL DEVELOPMENT TIME AND COSTS, AND FREEING UP RESOURCES THAT WOULD BE SPENT ON DEVELOPING A SPACECRAFT TO FOCUS ON CULTIVATING MISSION ENABLING TECHNOLOGIES.  THE GOAL IS TO HAVE A CYGNUS DERIVED EAM DEPLOYED IN CISLUNAR SPACE BEFORE 2020. THIS SPACECRAFT WILL BE THE FIRST BUILDING BLOCK IN SUPPORTING BOTH COMMERCIAL MARKETS AND GOVERNMENT OBJECTIVES. THE PROPOSED EFFORT FOR THIS NEXTSTEP BAA PHASE I, INVOLVES DEFINING AN EAM ARCHITECTURE AND CONCEPT OF OPERATIONS (CONOPS) THAT ADDRESSES COMMERCIAL MARKETS AND NASA EXPLORATION OBJECTIVES, TECHNOLOGY MATURATION PLANNING AND INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT, AND TO IDENTIFY TECHNOLOGIES THAT CAN BE IMPLEMENTED AND DEMONSTRATED IN THE ISSILEO ENVIRONMENT WITHIN THE NEXT THREE YEARS.  TO MATURE HABITATION TECHNOLOGIES, THE CONTRACTOR WILL IDENTIFY STATE OF THE ART (SOA) TECHNOLOGIES ACROSS NASA TECHNOLOGY AREAS (TAS) DEFINED IN THE NASA TECHNOLOGY ROADMAP.  FOCUS WILL BE ON MATURATION OF THE FOLLOWING TECHNOLOGIES    ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL AND LIFE SUPPORT SYSTEMS    ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING    SAFETY AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE AND HABITATION    THERMAL CONTROL SYSTEMS    AUTONOMOUS HABITATION SYSTEMS    NAVIGATION    SYSTEMS MANAGEMENT    DOCKING AND CAPTURE    MECHANISMS AND DEPLOYABLE HABITATION ELEMENTS

prime_award_base_transaction_description: EXPLORATION UPPER STAGE ENGINES  MSFC WILL PROCURE TEN (10) RL10 FLIGHT ENGINES FROM AEROJET ROCKETDYNE, INC. TO SUPPORT THE SPACE LAUNCH SYSTEM (SLS) EXPLORATION MISSIONS 2 AND 3 (EM-2 AND EM-3). EACH FLIGHT WILL REQUIRE A FOUR (4) ENGINE CLUSTER. ADDITIONALLY, TWO (2) SPARE ENGINES WILL BE PROCURED. prime_award_base_transaction_description: THE LUCY SPACECRAFT AND MISSION OPERATIONS CONTRACT EMBODIES THE MISSION'S REQUIREMENT TO DESIGN, DEVELOPMENT, TEST, AND OPERATE THE LUCY SPACECRAFT BUS. LUCY WILL EXPLORE SIX JUPITER TROJAN ASTEROIDS TRAPPED BY JUPITERS GRAVITY IN TWO SWARMS THAT SHARE THE PLANETS ORBIT, ONE LEADING AND ONE TRAILING JUPITER IN ITS 12-YEAR CIRCUIT AROUND THE SUN. THE TROJANS ARE THOUGHT TO BE RELICS OF A MUCH EARLIER ERA IN THE HISTORY OF THE SOLAR SYSTEM, AND MAY HAVE FORMED FAR BEYOND JUPITERS CURRENT ORBIT.

prime_award_naics_description: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT IN THE PHYSICAL, ENGINEERING, AND LIFE SCIENCES (EXCEPT NANOTECHNOLOGY AND BIOTECHNOLOGY)
subawardee_business_types: U.S. STATE GOVERNMENT,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,STATE CONTROLLED INSTITUTION OF HIGHER LEARNING,SCHOOL OF FORESTRY
subaward_description:
CLEMSON UNIVERSITY SHALL PARTICIPATE IN THE COSI PROJECT DURING PHASE C/D WITH INVOLVEMENT OF THREE CLEMSON FACULTY MEMBERS: DIETER HARTMANN, MARCO AJELLO, AND MARK LEISING.  SPECIFIC SCIENTIFIC LEADERSHIP ROLES HAVE BEEN ASSIGNED TO HARTMANN AND AJELLO DURING PHASE B WITH HARTMANN BEING A MEMBER OF THE COSI SCIENCE STEERING COMMITTEE (CSSC), CO-LEAD OF THE GAMMA-RAY BURST (GRB) SUBGROUP AND AJELLO BEING THE LEAD OF THE EXTRAGALACTIC SUBGROUP.  ADDITIONALLY, LEISING IS AN EXPERT IN GAMMA-RAY EMISSION FROM NOVAE AND TYPE IA SUPERNOVAE (INCLUDING PUBLISHING A PAPER WITH COSI SENSITIVITY ESTIMATES DURING PHASE A), AND HARTMANN IS WELL-VERSED IN BROAD ASPECTS OF THE ASTROPHYSICS OF RADIOACTIVITY FROM CORE COLLAPSE SUPERNOVAE AND THEIR MIXING IN THE INTERSTELLAR MEDIUM.  ALL OF THESE SCIENCE TOPICS ARE HIGHLY RELEVANT FOR COSI.

CLEMSON WILL SUPPORT THE DATA PIPELINE AND ANALYSIS EFFORT.  THIS WILL INCLUDE DEVELOPMENT OF THE SOURCE LOCALIZATION SOFTWARE FOR SOURCES OF ALL TYPES (TRANSIENT, VARIABLE, AND PERSISTENT).  CLEMSON WILL CARRY OUT ANALYSIS TO DETERMINE THE OPTIMAL SELECTION OF DATA TO BE AUTOMATICALLY DOWNLINKED VIA THE TRACKING AND DATA RELAY SATELLITE SYSTEM (TDRSS) AND WILL PARTICIPATE IN DEVELOPING THE AUTOMATIC PROCESSING OF THE DATA ON GROUND. CLEMSON WILL ALSO PARTICIPATE IN WORK ON THE COSI BACKGROUND MODEL BY DEVELOPING METHODS FOR IDENTIFYING BACKGROUND EVENTS.

CLEMSON WILL SUPPORT OVERALL PIPELINE AND ANALYSIS SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT, TESTING, AND DEBUGGING, INCLUDING INPUT INTO THE COSI DATA CHALLENGES.  PRESENTING STATUS UPDATES AND RESULTS AT RELEVANT MEETINGS, SUPPORTING PIPELINE REVIEWS, AND PREPARING SOFTWARE DOCUMENTATION ARE INCLUDED IN THE CLEMSON EFFORT.

IT IS EXPECTED THAT CLEMSON TEAM MEMBERS WILL ATTEND CONFERENCES TO GIVE COSI PRESENTATIONS AND TO PUBLISH CONFERENCE PROCEEDINGS AND PREPARE MANUSCRIPTS FOR REFEREED PUBLICATIONS WHEN APPROPRIATE.

subaward_description:
NGSC SHALL FURNISH PERSONNEL AND ENGINEERING SERVICES NECESSARY TO FULLY DEVELOP THE
PAYLOAD INTERFACE PLATE (PIP) DESIGN (AS PRESENTED BY NGSC IN THE 12/14/2023 ENGINEERING
PEER REVIEW (EPR) MEETING), BUILD AND TEST THE PAYLOAD INTERFACE PLATE (PIP) PRIMARY
STRUCTURE, INCLUDING BIPODS, FOR THE COMPTON SPECTROMETER AND IMAGER (COSI) PROGRAM.

THIS SCOPE OF WORK INCLUDES A COLLABORATIVE ENGINEERING EFFORT BETWEEN NGSC AND
UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA BERKELEY (UCB). NGSC WILL MATURE THE PAYLOAD INTERFACE PLATE
(PIP) STRUCTURE AND SUPPORT SYSTEMS ENGINEERING ACTIVITIES FOR THE COSI PAYLOAD. FOCUS WILL
BE PLACED ON DESIGNING A STRUCTURE THAT MEETS UCBS NEED FOR MASS, MODAL AND STRENGTH
PERFORMANCE.

subaward_description: DR. SCHUMACHER, MR. FUNK, AND THE GRADUATE STUDENT WILL PRODUCE GROUND VALIDATION PRODUCTS USING LONG-TERM PROFILER DATA SETS FROM AUSTRALIA, THE AMAZON, OKLAHOMA, TEXAS, AND ALABAMA. THE PRODUCTS WILL BE USED TO ASSESS THE EFFICACY OF THE D-TRAIN SATELLITE ALGORITHM AND ITS RETRIEVALS OF VERTICAL MOTION AND MASS FLUX IN A VARIETY OF STORM TYPES AND TROPICAL AND MID-LATITUDE ENVIRONMENTS. DR. SCHUMACHER AND HER TEAM WILL ALSO PLAY AN ACTIVE ROLE IN THE PLANNING AND IMPLEMENTATION OF THE GROUND VALIDATION IOP(S) IN HOUSTON AND FLORIDA AND THE POSTIOP ANALYSIS.

MACE WILL EXTRACT, EXISTING SATELLITE NADIR-POINTING KA-BAND RADAR DATA AND ASSOCIATED RETRIEVALS OF CONDENSED-WATER PROFILES ALONG WITH THEIR UNCERTAINTIES, SO THAT THESE COINCIDENCE DATA SETS CAN BE USED AS A REFERENCE FOR INCUSS 2B-MASS AND 2B-MASS-RATE PRODUCTS. prime_award_base_transaction_description: THE EXPLORATION AND SPACE COMMUNICATIONS PROJECTS DIVISION (ESC) IS A NATIONAL RESOURCE LOCATED AT GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER (GSFC) WHICH ENABLES SCIENTIFIC DISCOVERY AND SPACE EXPLORATION BY PROVIDING INNOVATIVE AND MISSION-EFFECTIVE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS AND NAVIGATION SOLUTIONS TO A LARGE COMMUNITY OF DIVERSE CUSTOMERS.  ESC MANAGES OPERATIONAL GEOSTATIONARY COMMUNICATIONS RELAY SATELLITES AND GROUND SYSTEMS FOR THE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS AND NAVIGATION (SCAN) PROGRAM AT NASA HEADQUARTERS.  TODAY, SCAN NETWORK SYSTEMS CONSIST OF THE SPACE NETWORK (SN), THE NEAR EARTH NETWORK (NEN), AND THE DEEP SPACE NETWORK (DSN).  THE DAY-TO-DAY MANAGEMENT OF THESE THREE NETWORKS IS CURRENTLY NOT FULLY CONSISTENT. IT IS THE INTENTION OF THE GOVERNMENT TO UNIFY THE SN AND NEN WHERE PRACTICABLE UNDER THIS CONTRACT USING INTEGRATED, COMMON MANAGEMENT PRACTICES AND NETWORK SOLUTIONS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: THE EXPLORATION AND SPACE COMMUNICATIONS PROJECTS DIVISION (ESC) IS A NATIONAL RESOURCE LOCATED AT GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER (GSFC) WHICH ENABLES SCIENTIFIC DISCOVERY AND SPACE EXPLORATION BY PROVIDING INNOVATIVE AND MISSION-EFFECTIVE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS AND NAVIGATION SOLUTIONS TO A LARGE COMMUNITY OF DIVERSE CUSTOMERS.  ESC MANAGES OPERATIONAL GEOSTATIONARY COMMUNICATIONS RELAY SATELLITES AND GROUND SYSTEMS FOR THE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS AND NAVIGATION (SCAN) PROGRAM AT NASA HEADQUARTERS.  TODAY, SCAN NETWORK SYSTEMS CONSIST OF THE SPACE NETWORK (SN), THE NEAR EARTH NETWORK (NEN), AND THE DEEP SPACE NETWORK (DSN).  THE DAY-TO-DAY MANAGEMENT OF THESE THREE NETWORKS IS CURRENTLY NOT FULLY CONSISTENT. IT IS THE INTENTION OF THE GOVERNMENT TO UNIFY THE SN AND NEN WHERE PRACTICABLE UNDER THIS CONTRACT USING INTEGRATED, COMMON MANAGEMENT PRACTICES AND NETWORK SOLUTIONS.
prime_award_naics_description: ALL OTHER TELECOMMUNICATIONS

prime_award_program_activities_funding_t: 0001: SPACE OPERATIONS (DIRECT)
prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF THE COMMERCIAL CREW PROGRAM (CCP) COMMERCIAL CREW TRANSPORTATION CAPABILITY (CCTCAP) CONTRACT WILL PROVIDE COMPLETION OF THE DESIGN, DEVELOPMENT, TEST, EVALUATION, AND CERTIFICATION OF AN INTEGRATED CREW TRANSPORTATION SYSTEM (CTS) CAPABLE OF TRANSPORTING NASA CREW TO AND FROM THE ISS, IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE DESIGN REFERENCE MISSIONS AND NASA'S CERTIFICATION STANDARDS AND REQUIREMENTS. CERTIFICATION OF THE CTS WILL BE DETERMINED BY NASA. NASA PLANS TO ISSUE TASK ORDERS FOR POST CERTIFICATION MISSIONS (PCM) TO AND FROM ISS THAT INCLUDE GROUND, LAUNCH, LIFEBOAT, ON-ORBIT, RETURN AND RECOVERY OPERATIONS. THE MINIMUM QUANTITY OF MISSIONS TO BE ORDERED IS TWO (2) AND THE MAXIMUM POTENTIAL QUANTITY OF MISSIONS WHICH MAY BE ORDERED IS SIX (6). IN ADDITION, NASA MAY ISSUE TASK ORDERS FOR SPECIAL STUDIES USED FOR RISK REDUCTION AND OTHER PURPOSES RELATED TO THE CTS. NASA CERTIFICATION UNDER CLIN 001 IS COMPLETE WHEN THE CONTRACTOR'S CREW TRANSPORTATION SYSTEM (CTS) HAS MET NASA S REQUIREMENTS FOR SAFELY TRANSPORTING CREW TO AND FROM THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION (ISS) IN ACCORDANCE WITH DOCUMENTS IDENTIFIED IN SECTION C.1, SPECIFICATIONS/STATEMENT OF WORK. SUBCLINS 001A AND 001B, IDENTIFIED IN TABLE B.3, DDTE/CERTIFICATION SUBCLINS, ARE DELIVERY MILESTONES THAT REPRESENT COMPLETION OF REQUIRED WORK NECESSARY TO ACHIEVE NASA CERTIFICATION. DELIVERY PAYMENT FOR THE ISS DESIGN CERTIFICATION REVIEW (DCR) FOR THE CREWED FLIGHT TO THE ISS INCLUDES ALL WORK UNDER THIS CLIN THAT OCCURS FROM THE CONTRACT EFFECTIVE DATE THROUGH THE ISS DCR COMPLETION. THE DELIVERY PAYMENT FOR THE CERTIFICATION REVIEW (CR) WILL INCLUDE ALL WORK THAT OCCURS FROMTHE ISS DCR DELIVERY DATE THROUGH THE END OF THE DDTE/CERTIFICATION CLIN 001. IN ACCORDANCE WITH CLAUSE C.1, SPECIFICATION/STATEMENT OF WORK, THE TASK ORDERING PROCEDURES AND OTHER TERMS AND CONDITIONS IN THE CONTRACT, THE CONTRACTING OFFICER MAY ISSUE POST CERTIFICATION MISSION (PCM) TASK ORDERS. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL USE THE MISSION PRICING RATES SHOWN IN TABLE B.4.1, POST CERTIFICATION MISSION PRICES. THE PER MISSION PRICES ARE FOR A SINGLE ORDER AT THE PRICE STATED PER THE CALENDAR YEAR (CY) BASED ON THE NUMBER OF MISSIONS ORDERED. CTS FULL MISSION CAPABILITY PRICES SHALL BE BASED ON (1) FULFILLMENT OF THE DESIGN REFERENCE MISSION TO THE ISS FOUND IN CCT-DRM-1110, CREW TRANSPORTATION SYSTEM DESIGN REFERENCE MISSIONS, ATTACHMENT J-03, CONTRACT PERFORMANCE WORK STATEMENT, AND OTHER TERMS AND CONDITIONS IN THE CONTRACT AND (2) ALL INHERENT CTS CAPABILITIES THAT ARE WITHIN THE PROPOSED MISSION PRICES. IN ACCORDANCE WITH ATTACHMENT J-03, CONTRACT PERFORMANCE WORK STATEMENT, THE TASK ORDERING PROCEDURES AND OTHER TERMS AND CONDITIONS IN THE CONTRACT, THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PERFORM SPECIAL STUDIES, TEST AND ANALYSES, AS INITIATED BY WRITTEN DIRECTION FROM THE CONTRACTING OFFICER. BOEING CCTCAP POST CERTIFICATION MISSION 1 (PCM-1) TASK ORDER AGAINST NNK14MA75C CLIN 002, AS DESCRIBED IN CLAUSE B.4 POST CERTIFICATION MISSIONS (IDIQ)(CLIN 002) AND ALL OTHER APPLICABLE TERMS AND CONDITIONS.
prime_award_naics_description: GUIDED MISSILE AND SPACE VEHICLE MANUFACTURING

prime_award_base_transaction_description: LIBERA, EARTH VENTURE CONTINUITY 1  MISSION. PROVIDE AN INSTRUMENT TO BE INTEGRATED ON THE UPCOMING JOINT POLAR SATELLITE SYSTEM-3 SATELLITE THAT WILL MEASURE SHORT WAVE LONG WAVE AND TOTAL RADIATION AT TOP OF THE ATMOSPHERE
prime_award_naics_description: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT IN THE PHYSICAL, ENGINEERING, AND LIFE SCIENCES (EXCEPT NANOTECHNOLOGY AND BIOTECHNOLOGY)
subaward_description:
THE LIBERA MISSION IS A NASA FUNDED PROJECT THAT WILL BE DESIGNED, AND BUILT BY THE LABORATORY
FOR ATMOSPHERIC AND SPACE PHYSICS (LASP) AT THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO, BOULDER. LIBERA IS
PLANNED TO FLY ON-BOARD THE NASA/NATIONAL OCEANOGRAPHIC AND ATMOSPHERIC ADMINISTRATION
(NOAA) JOINT POLAR SATELLITE SYSTEM  3 (JPSS-3) SATELLITE, SCHEDULED FOR LAUNCH IN 2027, WITH A
FIVE-YEAR PRIME MISSION LIFE. THE PRIMARY GOAL IS TO DEMONSTRATE A METHOD FOR THE SEAMLESS
EXTENSION OF THE EARTH RADIATION BUDGET (ERB) RECORD, ESSENTIAL FOR RECOGNIZING CHANGES TO EARTHS
CLIMATE SYSTEM AND FOR CONSTRAINING FUTURE PREDICTIONS. THE LIBERA MISSION IS A CLASS C PROGRAM.
LIBERA WAS SELECTED UNDER THE NASA EARTH VENTURE CONTINUITY-1 ANNOUNCEMENT OF OPPORTUNITY
(AO) NNH17ZDA004O-EVC1, A PROGRAM ELEMENT APPENDIX OF THE THIRD STAND-ALONE MISSIONS
OF OPPORTUNITY (SALMON-3) NOTICE. THE EVC-1 AO SOLICITED PROPOSALS FOR COMPLETE PRINCIPAL
INVESTIGATOR (PI)-LED COST-CAPPED MISSIONS TO DEMONSTRATE A MEANS FOR PROVIDING CONTINUITY OF
NASA'S EARTH RADIATION BUDGET (ERB) CLIMATE DATA RECORDS THROUGH THE DESIGN, IMPLEMENTATION,
ON-ORBIT CHARACTERIZATION AND SCIENTIFIC EXPLOITATION OF A SUITABLE, CAPABLE OBSERVING SYSTEM.
LIBERA IS A NADIR POINTING INSTRUMENT. THE LIBERA AZIMUTH ACTUATOR ROTATES THE ENTIRE INSTRUMENT
IN THE AZIMUTH DIRECTION TO ALLOWING LIBERAS RADIOMETERS TO SCAN ACROSS THE EARTH AT DIFFERENT
VIEWING ANGLES. THE BRUSHLESS DC (BLDC) ACTUATOR, WHICH IS NEARLY IDENTICAL TO THE TSIS BLDC
ACTUATOR, WILL BE INCORPORATED INTO THE INSTRUMENT BY LASP AND WILL PROVIDE PRECISION POINTING FOR
LIBERA.

subaward_description: THIS STATEMENT OF WORK DESCRIBES THE SCOPE OF WORK TO BE PERFORMED BY CO-INVESTIGATOR, DR. THOMAS H. VONDERHAAR AND HIS TEAM UNDER THE LIBERA PROJECT. HE WILL ADVISE AND AID DEVELOPMENT OF LIBERA DATA PROCESSING AND SCIENCE METHODS, ALGORITHMS AND PRODUCTS. AND PROVIDE ADVICE BASED UPON PREVIOUS EARTH RADIATION BUDGET (ERB) RESEARCH AND EXPERIENCE WITH THE INSTRUMENT-ALGORITHM-PRODUCT-SCIENCE PROCESS. AS NEEDED HE WILL ASSIST STUDENTS, POSTDOCS AND OTHER LIBERA SCIENCE TEAM MEMBERS WITH THEIR EFFORTS. HE WILL CONTRIBUTE TO TEAM REPORTS AND PUBLICATIONS. HE WORKS MAINLY IN AN ADVISORY CAPACITY.
